Builds and installs the ctx-* tooling binaries (ctx-context, ctx-scan, ctx-verify, ctx-cage, ctx-run, ctx-summarize, ctx-brief, ctx-status) into `target/debug` by compiling them from a CTX repo and copying the artifacts.

The script locates the CTX repo via the first argument, the `CTX_REPO` environment variable, or defaults to `../CTX` (sibling directory). It validates the path by checking for `crates/ctx-context/Cargo.toml` and exits with a clear error if missing. The ctx-cage package produces two binaries (ctx-cage and ctx-run) from a single Cargo.toml, so the script tracks packages and binaries separately to handle this mismatch.

This script handles only binary installation; prompt files needed at runtime by ctx-scan, ctx-summarize, and ctx-brief are synced separately by `scripts/update-template.sh`. Binaries are refreshed on every run to pick up tooling repo changes.